result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

The defendant Carrie L. Mueller was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Carrie L. Mueller in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 14CF62, 14CF206,  and 13CF82 @ 9:15 a.m. 13CF82 State withdraws motion to withdraw deferred judgment and extends 2 yrs - 6/9/17 @ 1:00 p.m. Def agrees, Court approves with same conditions. Agreement stated - 14CF62 - Def will plea to cts 1 & 2, ct 3 dismiss and read in, Ct 1 - Defer judgment 2 yrs, if no crimes to probable cause, cooperate with social services and successfully completes probation and pays all court obligations, will dismiss. Ct 2 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, cooperate with soc.services, counseling deemed necessary, cc. 14CF206 - amend ct 1 946.49 (1)(a), ct 1 withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, cooperate with social services, counseling deemed appropriate, cc. Ct 2 - defer judgment 2 yrs, no crimes to probable cause, successfully complete probation,  pay all court obligations, cooperate with soc.services, will dismiss if successfully completes. Atty Laufenberg agrees. Def agrees. 14CF62 ct 1 - no contest plea. Ct 2 - guilty. Ct 3 dismissed consistent with agreement. 14CF206 - ct 1 amended to misd bail jumping, guilty plea, ct 2 - guilty. Court reviews plea quest. and consitutional rights. Atty Laufenberg satisfied. Court finds Def understands, accepts pleas, finds guilty of cts 1 & 2 of 14CF62, ct 3 dismissed. 14CF206 finds guilty of ct 1 misd bail jumping and ct 2 felony bail jumping.
14CF62 ct 1 - 14CF206 ct 2 - deferred judgment 2 yrs, if no crimes to probable cause, cooperates with social services, pays all court obligations, and successfully completes probation will dismiss. Review 6/9/17 @ 1:00 p.m. Written agreement signed. 
Statement by Atty Laufenberg, letters given to the Court. Statement by Def. Court accepts agreement.
14CF62 ct 2 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, costs, cooperate with social services.
14CF206 ct 2 - withheld sentence, 1  yr probation, concurrent, cooperate with soc. services, costs. Counseling as deemed appropriate on both.
  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.
Signature bonds continue. Postconviction rights.

Defendant Carrie L. Mueller in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called 13CF82, 14CF62 and 14CF206 @10:55 a.m. Def waives prelim in 14CF206. Court reviews prelim rights, Court finds accepts waiver, finds probable cause and Def bound over. Information filed. Copy received, reading waived, reserve all juris. objections, not guilty pleas to all cts. Bond continues.  Status conference scheduled for March 11, 2015 at 09:30 am.
